Class Members :-
Fields and methods inside classes are often referred to as "Class Members".
Fields :-
Variables inside a class are called fields, and that you can access them by creating an object of the class, and by using the dot syntax (.).

class MyClass
{
  // Class members
  string color = "red";        // field
  int maxSpeed = 200;          // field
  public void fullThrottle()   // method
  {
    Console.WriteLine("The car is going as fast as it can!");
  }
}
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Creating multiple objects of one class:

class car
    {
        string wheels;
        int speed;
        static void Main()
        {
            car FORD =new car();
            FORD.wheels="four";
            FORD.speed=300;

            car MERC =new car();
            MERC.wheels="ten";
            MERC.speed=400;

            Console.WriteLine(FORD.wheels);
            Console.WriteLine(MERC.speed);
        }
    }
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Object Methods :-
Methods normally belong to a class, and they define how an object of a class behaves.
The method must be public. And remember that we use the name of the method followed by two parentheses () and a semicolon ; to call (execute) the method.

class car
    {
        string wheels;
        int speed;
        public void fulltod()
        {
            Console.WriteLine("helllooo");
        }
        static void Main()
        {
            car FORD =new car();
            FORD.wheels="four";
            FORD.speed=300;

            car MERC =new car();
            MERC.wheels="ten";
            MERC.speed=400;

            Console.WriteLine(FORD.wheels);
            Console.WriteLine(MERC.speed);
            
            FORD.fulltod();
        }
    }
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
